11/06/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- General Jovan Lakcevic has been appointed the new chief of the Montenegrin Army's general staff, according to an announcement Friday (9 June). 
He had headed the Podgorica Corps. 
General Dragan Samardzic was appointed deputy chief of staff.
In other news Friday, Switzerland decided to recognise Montenegro as an independent state and to establish diplomatic ties with it. 
Formal notification is expected soon. 
(Mina, Beta - 09/06/06)
